.","meanings":["A perennially popular given name, of Continental Germanic origin, from <i>haim</i> ‘home’ + <i>rīc</i> ‘power, ruler’. It was an Old French name, adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain. It has been borne by eight kings of England. Not until the 17th century did the form <i>Henry</i> (as opposed to   Harry  ) become the standard vernacular form, mainly under the influence of the Latin form <i>Henricus</i> and French <i>Henri</i>."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Henry De Appleby III was born about 1275, in Appleby Magna, Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom as the son of Sir Henry de Appleby II. He married Alicia De Appleby about 1295, in Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. He died in 1296, in his hometown, at the age of 22."},"et":{"Abt 1275–1296":"umbes 1275–1296","1275–1296":"1275–1296","1277–Female":"1277–Surnud","1270–Female":"1270–Surnud","1296–1375":"1296–1375","1304–Male":"1304–Surnud","1250–1279":"1250–1279","1304":"1304","1279":"1279","1277":"1277","Abt 1275":"umbes 1275","1375":"1375","1275":"1275","1296":"1296","1250":"1250","1270":"1270","about 1295":"umbes 1295","Leicestershire, England":"Leicestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Over Appleby, Leicestershire, England":"Appleby Magna, Leicestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Appleby Magna, Leicestershire, England":"Appleby Magna, Leicestershire, England"},"fi":{"Abt 1275–1296":"noin 1275–1296","1275–1296":"1275–1296","1277–Female":"1277–Kuollut","1270–Female":"1270–Kuollut","1296–1375":"1296–1375","1304–Male":"1304–Kuollut","1250–1279":"1250–1279","1304":"1304","1279":"1279","1277":"1277","Abt 1275":"noin 1275","1375":"1375","1275":"1275","1296":"1296","1250":"1250","1270":"1270","about 1295":"noin 1295","Leicestershire, England":"Leicestershire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Over Appleby, Leicestershire, England":"Appleby Magna, Leicestershire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Appleby Magna, Leicestershir